It's not the Mansion, but we can
always have chicken wings at Hooters?

14:42.799 --> 14:44.800
Nah, this is my problem.

14:46.094 --> 14:47.636
I'll deal with it.

15:05.863 --> 15:07.948
- Hey, buddy.
- Johnny Drama.

15:08.032 --> 15:09.283
What the heck are you doing here?

15:09.742 --> 15:11.451
I want you to call up Hugh Hefner

15:11.536 --> 15:14.037
and tell him it was you
that freed the monkeys.

15:14.122 --> 15:15.872
When were you
at the Playboy Mansion, Ralph?

15:15.957 --> 15:19.001
That was over 10 years ago, honey.

15:20.545 --> 15:22.504
My life is different now, John.

15:22.589 --> 15:24.006
I'm a daddy.

15:26.050 --> 15:27.467
You know?

15:27.552 --> 15:29.761
- You crazy, fucker?
- Just make the call.

15:29.846 --> 15:31.471
I'm not into that game anymore, all right?

15:31.556 --> 15:33.390
- I got a new series now.
- Really?

15:33.474 --> 15:35.100
Well, you know, it's a pilot.

15:35.184 --> 15:37.102
But I don't know shit
about any monkeys, Drama.

15:37.186 --> 15:39.646
Bullshit. I remember you
screaming the PETA chant

15:39.731 --> 15:41.315
- right before you freed them.
- PETA?

15:41.399 --> 15:42.566
You got the wrong guy, asshole.

15:42.650 --> 15:44.109
I bought my wife a chinchilla coat.

15:44.193 --> 15:46.486
- If it wasn't you, then who did it?
- How should I know?

15:46.571 --> 15:48.071
We were drunk off our asses.

15:48.823 --> 15:51.199
Come on, Ralph. You're married.

15:51.284 --> 15:53.368
You got a family. You got a life.

15:53.453 --> 15:55.037
I got nothing but the Mansion.

15:55.288 --> 15:56.788
Can't you make the phone call?

15:56.873 --> 15:58.832
Drama, when it comes to the Mansion,

15:58.916 --> 16:00.250
it's every man for himself.

16:00.460 --> 16:02.169
But you said you're done with all that.

16:02.253 --> 16:04.671
I lied. I'm going tonight.

16:05.715 --> 16:07.174
I ought to kick your ass.

16:07.258 --> 16:08.800
You wanna try?

16:10.887 --> 16:12.387
I'll deal with you later.

16:12.472 --> 16:14.723
See you tonight, motherfucker!

16:16.184 --> 16:17.893
I hope so, John.

16:17.977 --> 16:20.020
Pound some Cuervo like the old days, huh?

16:31.991 --> 16:34.660
Turtle, you know you forgot to take
the price-tags off your pajamas?

16:34.744 --> 16:36.745
I didn't forget. I'm returning these Monday.

16:36.913 --> 16:38.121
Guy's a genius.

16:38.206 --> 16:41.667
What's the use of spending
$1,200 on PJs if nobody knows it?

16:42.126 --> 16:43.919
You're all class, Turtle.

16:47.715 --> 16:49.841
- Hey, Marvin.
- Eric, put Vince on the phone.

16:50.927 --> 16:52.803
It's Marvin. He wants to talk to you.

16:52.887 --> 16:54.429
He's right here!

16:57.392 --> 16:58.684
Hey, Marvin!

16:58.768 --> 17:01.853
When you asked me how much you could
spend on a house, what did I tell you?

17:01.938 --> 17:04.271
- You were a little vague.
- "Vague"? Bullshit!

17:04.357 --> 17:06.775
I told you you could spend $1 million.

17:06.858 --> 17:09.319
I'm spending less than that.
The bank is coming up with the rest.

17:09.444 --> 17:11.613
Vince, you cannot afford that house.

17:11.698 --> 17:13.865
At best, you could last
for a couple of months.

17:13.950 --> 17:17.202
Then what? You're gonna be
out on the street like your brother.

17:17.286 --> 17:18.286
And you know what?

17:18.371 --> 17:21.373
You don't have a younger brother
like you to mooch off.

17:21.457 --> 17:24.041
Marv, I can't hear you. You're breaking up.

17:24.127 --> 17:25.292
I'm up in the hills...

17:26.128 --> 17:27.212
He's angry.

17:42.478 --> 17:43.562
Where are you going, Ari?

17:45.064 --> 17:46.773
I have a meeting, so...

17:47.150 --> 17:48.775
At the Playboy Mansion?

17:53.072 --> 17:54.948
You know, Playboy Mansion,
strip clubs, whorehouses...

17:55.032 --> 17:57.576
I go where the meetings are.
It's my fucking job.

17:57.660 --> 18:00.120
I want three weeks in the south
of France with the children.

18:00.204 --> 18:01.955
Oh, my God, baby!

18:02.623 --> 18:04.958
- Of course you can go.
- With you.

18:05.835 --> 18:07.419
And if you're not home by 2:00 a. m.,

18:07.503 --> 18:08.920
I'm gonna be standing at the gate screaming,

18:09.005 --> 18:11.673
"Ari Gold, super agent, forgot his Viagra!"

18:12.925 --> 18:14.092
Sounds good.

18:17.305 --> 18:19.598
Can you pop your trunk, please?

18:20.391 --> 18:22.225
Trunk's broken, buddy.

18:27.815 --> 18:29.691
Pop your trunk, please.

18:31.527 --> 18:32.861
All right.

18:41.871 --> 18:43.955
- Pat!
- Drama, you wanna get out of there?

18:44.040 --> 18:45.957
Hey, we got another stowaway, partner.

18:47.835 --> 18:50.086
Pat, I've known you for, like, 10 years.

18:50.338 --> 18:51.713
Can't you guys let me slide?

18:51.798 --> 18:53.006
Not a shot in hell.

18:53.090 --> 18:56.593
Do you know bringing in stowaways
can get you banned for life?

18:56.677 --> 18:59.137
It's not their fault.
They didn't know I was in the car.

18:59.555 --> 19:01.223
Guys, it was my idea.

19:01.307 --> 19:02.641
- I told him to.
Don't listen to him.

19:02.725 --> 19:05.310
He's my kid brother
and he's trying to take the blame.

19:05.394 --> 19:06.645
Johnny.

19:06.729 --> 19:08.688
Go on, go have fun. Don't worry about me.

19:10.650 --> 19:12.108
My night's done.

19:12.193 --> 19:13.819
Can you call me a cab?

19:13.903 --> 19:16.446
Try using your thumb down on Sunset.

19:17.073 --> 19:18.198
Patrick.

20:03.119 --> 20:06.788
Would you look at all
the nice fake titties in this place?

20:06.873 --> 20:07.956
I thought you liked naturals.

20:08.040 --> 20:10.542
I believe in a woman's right to choose.

20:10.626 --> 20:14.087
- Nice pajamas.
- It's formal nightwear, but thank you.

20:14.171 --> 20:15.630
That's it, this is proof.

20:15.715 --> 20:17.632
God is definitely a man.

20:18.634 --> 20:20.510
Excuse me, sweetheart.

20:24.682 --> 20:26.099
Good luck returning those.

20:28.144 --> 20:29.811
Sorry.

20:31.314 --> 20:32.314
Fuck!

20:36.193 --> 20:37.485
Yeah!

20:38.237 --> 20:40.030
Hey, get out of the street, you faggot!

20:40.114 --> 20:43.158
- Nice legs, fudge packer!
- Fuck you!

20:43.242 --> 20:44.826
Right here, college boys!

20:49.332 --> 20:50.332
What?

20:50.416 --> 20:51.750
Yo, Drama.

20:51.834 --> 20:54.586
I detected a weakness in Hef's security detail.

20:54.670 --> 20:56.463
I'm not coming back.
I'm almost home already.

20:56.547 --> 20:57.839
I took care of you as always, all right?

20:57.924 --> 21:01.051
Just come back to where it all began,
the monkey cages.

21:01.844 --> 21:03.470
I know you don't
want to talk about it right now.

21:03.554 --> 21:05.472
I had an amazing meeting at Warner's.

21:05.556 --> 21:08.058
Ari, please don't ruin the Mansion.

21:08.142 --> 21:10.226
You're gonna want to hear this, believe me.

21:10.478 --> 21:11.811
You know what I want to hear?

21:11.896 --> 21:13.980
I want to hear what
the lovely Hef girls have to say.

21:14.065 --> 21:16.399
Look how rude you are,
with your back to these lovely ladies.

21:16.484 --> 21:17.943
They're better to look at than listen to.

21:18.027 --> 21:20.528
What do you got?
Sorry. What do you got for us?

21:20.613 --> 21:22.614
What does the middle "A" stand for, Ari?

21:22.698 --> 21:23.990
Arrogant?

21:24.075 --> 21:25.909
- Abrasive?
- Argumentative?

21:25.993 --> 21:28.036
- Annoying?
- Asshole?

21:28.120 --> 21:30.121
Et tu, Vinnie? Et tu?

21:36.879 --> 21:38.254
You okay?

21:40.383 --> 21:41.466
Good job, kid.

21:41.550 --> 21:42.968
- Hey, did you see Macchio?
- No.

21:43.052 --> 21:45.178
- Keep your eyes open.
- All right, come on.

21:45.805 --> 21:48.181
Yeah, well, the thing is,
once the show hits syndication,

21:48.265 --> 21:50.475
you got to like find
some tax deductions, you know.

21:50.559 --> 21:51.810
Vince, I'm telling you...

21:51.894 --> 21:54.479
Real estate? Best investment ever.

21:54.563 --> 21:56.189
See, if it's not acting,

21:56.273 --> 21:57.607
we'll make our money through real estate.

21:57.733 --> 21:59.484
I should start commissioning
some of your capital gains

21:59.568 --> 22:02.529
so I can start seeing
some income out of this relationship.

22:02.613 --> 22:04.239
Oh, shit. Miss April.

22:04.323 --> 22:06.574
Guys, I got to hide. I'll see you in a bit.

22:08.202 --> 22:09.911
Guy's got three houses, we don't have one.

22:09.996 --> 22:11.121
He's a worker, though, Vince.

22:11.205 --> 22:13.498
The guy does a TV show,
a radio show, he's a D.J.

22:13.582 --> 22:14.624
He does a million things.

22:14.709 --> 22:17.502
You do Aquaman,
you got five houses. Boom.

22:18.587 --> 22:20.338
Don't you need to be home to your wife, Ari?

22:20.423 --> 22:22.340
No, I make the goddamn rules.

22:23.009 --> 22:24.300
I got till 2:00.

22:24.385 --> 22:26.761
What are you saying? You're pissing me off!

22:26.846 --> 22:28.972
Don't get in my face.
What are you getting in my face about?

22:29.056 --> 22:30.849
- Just be a man and admit it!
- Johnny!

22:30.933 --> 22:32.934
- Admit you did it!
- I told you I didn't do it.

22:33.019 --> 22:34.019
- Admit it!
- I didn't do it!

22:34.103 --> 22:37.022
I already told you that,
you ex-evening soap star!

22:37.106 --> 22:39.858
- I did an indie, asshole!
- Excuse me. Johnny!

22:39.942 --> 22:42.527
Johnny Chase. The Monkey Boy.

22:42.611 --> 22:43.653
- Hef.
- Vince.

22:43.738 --> 22:45.947
- How are you?
- Good to see you.

22:46.032 --> 22:47.115
Johnny's my brother,

22:47.199 --> 22:49.617
and he swears it wasn't him
that let the monkeys free.

22:50.286 --> 22:51.745
Well, what's the real story, John?

22:51.829 --> 22:54.622
Well, Mr. Hefner, I'm not one to rat,

22:55.291 --> 22:56.916
but it was this guy that sprung the apes.

22:57.001 --> 22:58.418
With all due respect, Mr. Hefner,

22:58.502 --> 23:00.295
I never went near that zoo, never.

23:00.880 --> 23:03.089
Well, you boys better remember who did,

23:03.174 --> 23:05.300
or you're both out of here.

23:05.384 --> 23:06.593
It was a long time ago.

23:06.677 --> 23:08.053
And we were so drunk.

23:08.137 --> 23:10.472
We were sitting at that table
by The Grotto over there.

23:10.556 --> 23:12.265
We were banging out shots of Cuervo and...

23:12.349 --> 23:14.350
It was me and you and...

23:16.812 --> 23:18.438
Pauly!

23:18.522 --> 23:20.065
Let the fuck go of me!

23:20.149 --> 23:22.817
That's my fucking bad arm, you piece of shits!

23:22.902 --> 23:25.820
They shouldn't be locked up
in cages in this house and you know it.

23:25.905 --> 23:27.572
I'm gonna fucking get you, bro!

23:27.656 --> 23:29.908
- Get him out of here.
- Lifetime ban, Pauly.

23:29.992 --> 23:31.701
Oh, bro, no!

23:33.454 --> 23:35.580
I think he just called Hugh Hefner "bro. "

23:35.664 --> 23:37.123
I'm sorry, guys.

23:37.875 --> 23:39.542
Sorry, Vince.

23:39.627 --> 23:41.419
- Thank you, Mr. Hefner.
- You have a good time.

23:41.504 --> 23:44.130
- Thank you, Mr. Heffner.
- And behave yourselves.

23:44.215 --> 23:45.757
- We will.
I appreciate it.

23:45.841 --> 23:47.926
Thanks, Hef! Good night!

23:48.010 --> 23:49.219
Yes, I'm back.

23:49.845 --> 23:52.013
- Bro, thank you!
- Of course.

23:52.515 --> 23:54.349
Ralph, man, sorry about that.

23:54.433 --> 23:56.518
- I had you wrong.
- Come on, let's get a drink.

23:56.644 --> 23:59.145
Yeah, yeah, yeah. We'll talk about that pilot.

23:59.230 --> 24:01.356
Listen, there's nothing in it for you.

24:11.075 --> 24:14.244
Hey, Vince, we gonna throw parties
like this at the new house?

24:14.328 --> 24:17.122
No. E doesn't think we can
afford the new house.

24:17.206 --> 24:19.207
E's a fucking buzz kill.

24:19.291 --> 24:20.792
I thought you don't need all the toys, Vince?

24:20.876 --> 24:22.544
Yeah, I don't need them. I like them.

24:22.628 --> 24:24.963
The worst thing that happens
is they kick you out.

24:25.047 --> 24:27.715
They give you time
to pack up your shit, bro, trust me.

24:27.800 --> 24:29.175
They ain't kicking us out, all right?

24:29.260 --> 24:31.094
Vince is a superstar.

24:31.178 --> 24:32.804
If it ain't this, it's something else.

24:32.888 --> 24:35.723
M.C. Hammer could've used a guy
like you, Turtle, back in the day.

24:35.808 --> 24:38.434
I don't know about you,
but I'm in this for the long haul.

24:38.519 --> 24:40.645
Oh, yeah, what do you think we're in it for?

24:40.729 --> 24:44.065
Well, I don't know.
Did you really hate the script?

24:44.150 --> 24:45.859
No. I mean, I liked it.

24:46.527 --> 24:49.195
I don't wanna end up
looking like an idiot on the screen.

24:49.280 --> 24:51.322
Wow. I've never seen you this insecure.

24:51.407 --> 24:53.992
I'm not insecure.
I'm just not confident enough to think

24:54.076 --> 24:56.703
- that I can be a superhero.
- Now that I see an opening,

24:56.787 --> 24:59.414
Warner's is willing to bank $100 million

24:59.498 --> 25:02.000
on the fact that you are a superhero.

25:02.084 --> 25:04.127
They loved you so much in the meeting today,

25:04.211 --> 25:07.297
they want to shoot back-to-back movies,
like Lord ofthe Rings.

25:07.381 --> 25:10.216
